list.abstract: degree是一个英语单词，可以用作名词，可以翻译为程度、学位，等等。

yingyinNormal.en: Place the steam wand halfway in the pitcher at a 45-degree angle until the milk is 103 degrees.
yingyinNormal.zh: 把蒸汽管放到罐子的中间，成45度夹角 直到牛奶有103度热。

yingyinNormal.en: From over 800 feet up, the observation deck offers 360 degree views of the entire city.
yingyinNormal.zh: 您可以走上超过 244 米高的观景台，360 度环观市内全景。

yingyinNormal.en: His job is to make sure that each load of scrap is heated to a precise set of specifications, which means he's constantly on the move between a tiny air-conditioned control room and the 3,000-degree furnace.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他的工作就是确保每个负载的废金属加热，到设定一套明确的规范，这意味着他要一直运动在一间小空调掌控室里三千度的熔炉。

yingyinNormal.en: And I do not know to what degree you have been directly involved. But you will resolve it. Now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不知道你直接参与的程度多深。但你必须化解它。立即化解。

yingyinNormal.en: People like to say, "if you build it, they will come," and to a degree, that's true. You know, if you build it, that encourages people.
yingyinNormal.zh: 人们总是说,只要你建起来了,他们就会来的从某种程度上讲那是正确的。你想,你建成了,就会吸引人们的到来。

yingyinNormal.en: I have a master's degree. Who doesn't?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我有个硕士文凭的。谁没有啊？

yingyinNormal.en: I believe the law degree in my pocket says so.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我口袋里的法律学位可以证明我是。

yingyinNormal.en: Nobody does anything worth doing without a degree.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没有学位的人做不了大事。

yingyinNormal.en: Excuse me, what, a degree is a waste of time now? So...
yingyinNormal.zh: 我打断一下，什么？完成学位是浪费时间？所以...

yingyinNormal.en: Nobody does anything worth doing with a degree. No woman, anyway.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有学位的人也做不了大事，反正不会是女人。

yingyinNormal.en: What? Okay, enough with the third degree. I don't live here anymore.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么？ 好，别拷问我了我，我不住这里了。

yingyinNormal.en: You don't mean that. Well, what's she going to do with an English degree?
yingyinNormal.zh: 别这么说。她修这个英语学位有什么用?

yingyinNormal.en: I doubt you'd understand. Sheldon tells me you only have a master's degree.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我怀疑你听不听得懂，谢尔顿告诉我你只有个硕士学位。

yingyinNormal.en: Because none of us would be here without our degree, you do realize that, don't you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为没有学位我们任何一个都不会在这，你有意识到这点，对吗?

yingyinNormal.en: Getting divorced again. Getting my master's degree. Finally getting the job I wanted.
yingyinNormal.zh: 再次离婚，获得硕士学位，总算找到心仪的工作。

yingyinNormal.en: And, Jules, Becky was a huge help in this. You know she has a business degree from Penn?
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有，朱尔斯，贝琪在这里帮了很多忙，你知道她是宾夕法尼亚大学的商学位吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Dr. Jekyll's other personality was Mr. Hyde. Mr. Hyde. Didn't have a postgraduate degree.
yingyinNormal.zh: 杰基尔博士的另一重人格可是海德先生。海德"先生"啊。他连研究生学位都没有。

yingyinNormal.en: Now can you believe it? After only five years of playing football, I got a college degree.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你相信不相信？只不过玩了五年足球，我得到了大学学位。

yingyinNormal.en: Once in high school, but I dozed off and woke up with second-degree chemical burns on my face.
yingyinNormal.zh: 高中时候试过一次，后来打盹醒来之后，我脸上就二级化学灼伤了。

yingyinNormal.en: "All right, I tried." That should be the title of your autobiography. Ooh, a second-degree burn.
yingyinNormal.zh: “好吧，我尽力了”，你应该用这句当你自传的书名。有人被损得皮焦肉烂啦。

sense_info_list.en: the qualification given to a student after he or she has completed his or her studies

examination_example.sentence: His parents' good life has little to do with a college <highlight>degree</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他父母的优渥生活与大学学历关系不大。

examination_example.sentence: I still grew up in an upper middle-class home with parents who didn't have college <highlight>degrees</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我仍然在一个中上阶层家庭长大，父母没有大学学历。

examination_example.sentence: A quarter of America's public-sector workers have a university <highlight>degree</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 四分之一的美国公共部门员工拥有大学学位。

examination_example.sentence: Then they rated the <highlight>degree</highlight> which they had used intuition.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然后，他们评估了自己运用直觉的程度。

examination_example.sentence: It is hard to get right, and requires a remarkable <highlight>degree</highlight> of vision.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这很难做对，需要高度的远见。

examination_example.sentence: And I felt like that again, to a certain <highlight>degree</highlight>, when people responded to the blog so well.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在某种程度上，当人们对博客的反应如此之好时，我又有了这种感觉。

sense_info_list.en: the qualification given to a student after he or she has completed his or her studies

examination_example.sentence: I struggled (挣扎) to communicate in broken German and signed up to study in Germany to complete my <highlight>degree</highlight>.

examination_example.sentence: She did a <highlight>degree</highlight> in theater and then moved to Los Angeles.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她获得了戏剧学位，然后搬到了洛杉矶。

examination_example.sentence: They told me that I had to study for a <highlight>degree</highlight> so that I would achieve a career.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们告诉我，我必须攻读学位，这样我才能成就一番事业。

examination_example.sentence: To a certain <highlight>degree</highlight>, we can understand and control our experience of time passing.
